This is a simple Node.js Express application that serves static HTML files and allows users to create and view user data stored in a text file.

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   https://github.com/prabha2612/Node_assign3.git

2. Navigate to the project directory:
   cd Assign3

3. Install dependencies:
   npm install
##Requirements
 - install Nodejs 
 - install nodemon 
 - install express 
 - install body-parser

## Dependencies
Express: Fast, unopinionated, minimalist web framework for Node.js.
body-parser: Node.js body parsing middleware.
fs: Node.js file system module for reading and writing files.


## File Structure
app.js: Main entry point of the application.
htmlfiles/: Directory containing static HTML files served by the application.
index.html: Home page of the application.
create.html: Form for adding a new user.
users.html: Page displaying the list of users.
users.txt: Text file where user data is stored.

